  "stimulus_html": "<p><i>β</i>-Ocimene is a pleasant-smelling hydrocarbon found in the leaves of certain herbs. It has the molecular formula C<sub>10</sub>H<sub>16</sub> and a UV absorption maximum at 232 nm. On hydrogenation with a palladium catalyst, 2,6-dimethyloctane is obtained. Ozonolysis of <i>β</i>-ocimene, followed by treatment with zinc and acetic acid, produces the following four fragments:</p>\n<img class=\"scaled-down\" src=\"https://exercises.openstax.org/rails/active_storage/blobs/proxy/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBZ0FWIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--ee5dc2cafb3b71c5d6f0ae4be5438ea26a5d206f/OChem_14_EC_026.jpg\" alt=\"The structures of acetone, formaldehyde, pyruvaldehyde, and malonaldehyde.\">",
